CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 25, 1961, pg. 15, reads: "NAACP Young Adult Leaders - Above are the newly elected officers of the Young Adults Chapter of the NAACP. Left to right, seated: Carole VeLar, recording secretary; Emmett Woods, president, and Marlene Stevens, corresponding secretary. Standing: Vann Johnson, historian; Mrs. Dorothy Williams, general adviser, James Tyler, first vice president; Barbara Williams, treasurer, and Timothy Ivey, second vice president. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Young Adult Chapter of NAACP officers, seated from left: Carole VeLar, Emmett Woods, Marlene Stevens; standing: Vann Johnson, Dorothy Williams, James Tyler, Barbara Williams, and Timothy Ivey posed behind table
